    "Max-pooling extracts the maximum from this activation map Definition 7 (Dilated Subseries) A dilated subseries, denoted by A i,l,d, is a sequence extracted from a time series A = (a 1,.",
    ", a n), with 1 ≤ i < i + l × d ≤ m. This subseries has length l and dilation factor d, and it includes l non-contiguous points from A starting at offset i and taking every d-th value as follows:",
    "A i,l,d = (a i, a i+d×1,.",
    ", a i+d×(l-1))",
    "The dilation technique is used in convolution-based, shapelet-based and dictionarybased models."
  ],
